summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2011 CHEVROLET EQUINOX. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE VEHICLE STALLED AND HESITATED TO ACCELERATE WHEN THE ACCELERATOR PEDAL WAS DEPRESSED. A DIAGNOSTIC WAS PERFORMED BY A DEALER, WHO STATED THAT THE HIGH PRESSURE FUEL PUMP WAS LEAKING GASOLINE INTO THE MOTOR OIL. THE VEHICLE WAS REPAIRED. THE DETAILS OF THE REPAIR WERE UNKNOWN. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT MADE AWARE OF THE FAILURE.  THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 11,000. THE CURRENT MILEAGE WAS 11,100.     UPDATED 7/15/13 *CN
